column61: a few conifers, but mostly (90%) deciduous. Surrounding area was logged in the past. Pool is in a rocky ridgetop bowl. Lots of ferns in northern part of pool, plus some sphagnum moss. The south end is deeper with less vegetation. Very dark tannic water.
column105: more than 5 wood frog tadpoles in pool; it was difficult to see in the dark tannic water so I didn't spend a lot of time trying to find more. Salamander egg masses looked like they were about a week away from emerging.
